The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Mendis is new CEO
Colombo: The Sri Lankan cricket board Wednesday formally announced the appointment of former national captain and hard-hitting batsman Duleep Mendis as its new chief executive officer (CEO). Sri Lanka Cricket (SLC) said in a statement that Mendis replaces Anura Tennakoon from January 1 2004. Mendis, 51, made his Test debut against England during Sri Lankas inaugural Test in 1982, and went on to play 24 Tests and 79 ODIs. (AP)  Copyright 
